exposed-jdbc/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Exposed is JetBrains' Kotlin SQL framework for building type-safe database queries and persistence code. The exposed-jdbc module provides the blocking JDBC integration, including database connections, transactions, schema utilities, and statement execution.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-core/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Exposed Core is the base module of JetBrains Exposed, a Kotlin SQL/ORM framework that provides the type-safe SQL DSL, table and column model, expressions, statements, and vendor dialect abstractions. It supplies the shared schema and query-building primitives used by the Exposed JDBC/R2DBC and DAO modules to work with relational databases from Kotlin applications.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-core/index.json:27:    \"description\" : \"Exposed Core is the base module of JetBrains Exposed, a Kotlin SQL/ORM framework for building type-safe database code. It provides the SQL DSL primitives, schema and table model, expressions, statements, and dialect abstractions used by Exposed's JDBC, R2DBC, and DAO modules.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-core/index.json:45:    \"description\" : \"Exposed Core is the base module of JetBrains Exposed, a Kotlin SQL/ORM framework for building type-safe database code. It provides the SQL DSL primitives, schema and table model, expressions, statements, and dialect abstractions used by Exposed's JDBC, R2DBC, and DAO modules.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-core/index.json:63:    \"description\" : \"Exposed Core is the base module of JetBrains Exposed, a Kotlin SQL/ORM framework for building type-safe database code. It provides the SQL DSL primitives, schema and table model, expressions, statements, and dialect abstractions used by Exposed's JDBC, R2DBC, and DAO modules.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-core/index.json:81:    \"description\" : \"Exposed Core is the base module of JetBrains Exposed, a Kotlin SQL/ORM framework for building type-safe database code. It provides the SQL DSL primitives, schema and table model, expressions, statements, and dialect abstractions used by Exposed's JDBC, R2DBC, and DAO modules.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-json/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Exposed JSON extends JetBrains Exposed with Kotlin APIs for mapping database JSON and JSONB columns to serialized application types. It provides column definitions and JSON path helpers for storing, querying, and extracting structured JSON values across supported SQL databases.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.exposed/exposed-kotlin-datetime/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Exposed is a lightweight SQL library and ORM framework for Kotlin that offers a type-safe SQL DSL and DAO API. The exposed-kotlin-datetime module adds Exposed date-time column types and SQL functions based on the kotlinx-datetime library.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.module/jackson-module-kotlin/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson module that adds support for serializing and deserializing Kotlin classes and data classes. It lets Jackson infer constructor parameter names and work with single-constructor classes without requiring explicit property name annotations or default constructors.\",\n./metadata/co.touchlab/stately-concurrency/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"The published root JAR contains Kotlin metadata/linkdata and no JVM class files; Gradle module metadata redirects JVM variants to co.touchlab:stately-concurrency-jvm:2.1.0.\",\n./metadata/co.touchlab/stately-strict/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"The published root JAR contains Kotlin metadata/linkdata and no JVM class files; Gradle module metadata redirects JVM variants to co.touchlab:stately-strict-jvm:2.1.0.\",\n./metadata/co.touchlab/stately-concurrent-collections/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"The published root JAR contains Kotlin metadata/linkdata and no JVM class files; Gradle module metadata redirects JVM variants to co.touchlab:stately-concurrent-collections-jvm:2.1.0.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-test/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlin-test is Kotlin's multiplatform testing library, providing common assertion functions and test annotations for Kotlin code. It integrates the shared kotlin.test API with platform test runners such as JUnit, JUnit 5, TestNG, JavaScript frameworks, and WebAssembly targets.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-daemon-embeddable/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"This artifact packages the Kotlin compiler daemon implementation for use with the embeddable compiler. It runs compilation work in a separate process so build tools and IDE integrations can invoke Kotlin compilation out of process.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-script-runtime/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides the core Kotlin scripting runtime types, including standard script templates and dependency-resolution APIs used by Kotlin scripts. It supplies the classes that other Kotlin scripting components and hosts rely on to compile, configure, and run .kts scripts.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-jvm/2.3.21/reachability-metadata.json:56:      \"type\" : \"kotlin.script.experimental.api.KotlinType\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Scripting JVM provides JVM-specific APIs and utilities for configuring, compiling, evaluating, caching, and running Kotlin scripts. It supplies JVM classpath, classloader, dependency, and REPL support used by Kotlin scripting hosts on the JVM.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-compiler-embeddable/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Scripting Compiler Embeddable packages the compiler plugin and REPL/script compilation implementation for use with the embeddable Kotlin compiler. It lets JVM tools, build systems, and scripting hosts configure, compile, and evaluate Kotlin scripts without depending on the standalone compiler distribution.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Standard Library for JVM provides the core runtime classes, collections, and extension APIs used by Kotlin applications on the JVM. It supports common programming tasks such as text handling, sequences, and Java interoperability required by compiled Kotlin code.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib/index.json:27:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Standard Library for JVM provides the core runtime classes, collections, and extension APIs used by Kotlin applications on the JVM. It supports common programming tasks such as text handling, sequences, and Java interoperability required by compiled Kotlin code.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-android-extensions-runtime/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Android Extensions Runtime provides the runtime annotations and interfaces used by the Kotlin Android Extensions compiler plugin for synthetic Android view access and Parcelable generation. It defines cache configuration, layout container support, and parcelization marker types that generated Kotlin Android code depends on at runtime.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-test-junit/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlin-test-junit adapts Kotlin's kotlin.test API to the JUnit 4 runner on the JVM. It provides the JUnit-specific asserter and annotation support that let Kotlin tests run under JUnit while using Kotlin's common test facade.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-reflect/1.7.10/reachability-metadata.json:51:        \"typeReached\": \"kotlin.reflect.jvm.internal.impl.descriptors.runtime.components.ReflectKotlinClass$Factory\"\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-reflect/1.7.10/reachability-metadata.json:120:        \"typeReached\": \"kotlin.reflect.jvm.internal.impl.builtins.KotlinBuiltIns\"\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-reflect/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlin-reflect is Kotlin's optional JVM runtime reflection library, providing full support for the kotlin.reflect API and related reflection extensions. It lets applications inspect Kotlin classes, functions, properties, and types at runtime without requiring reflection support in deployments that do not use it.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-common/2.3.21/reachability-metadata.json:156:          \"kotlin.script.experimental.annotations.KotlinScript\"\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-common/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Scripting Common provides shared scripting APIs for defining script sources, diagnostics, compilation and evaluation configurations, and REPL interactions. It supplies the common types used by Kotlin scripting hosts and compiler integrations to configure, compile, and evaluate Kotlin scripts.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-test-testng/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlin-test-testng supplies the TestNG integration for Kotlin's kotlin.test API on the JVM. It maps Kotlin test annotations and assertion reporting to TestNG so Kotlin test code can run under the TestNG runner.\",\n./stats/io.github.oshai/kotlin-logging-jvm/8.0.01/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/io.github.oshai/kotlin-logging-jvm/8.0.01/src/test/kotlin/io_github_oshai/kotlin_logging_jvm/Kotlin_logging_jvmTest.kt\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-parcelize-runtime/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Parcelize Runtime provides the annotations and helper types used by Kotlin's Parcelize compiler plugin to generate Android Parcelable implementations. It supplies APIs such as @Parcelize, Parceler, TypeParceler, RawValue, and parcelableCreator that generated Kotlin Android code references at compile time and runtime.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-jdk7/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Kotlin Standard Library JDK 7 adds JVM standard library extensions that rely on Java 7