[thinking] I'm thinking about how the Kotlin plugin compiles Kotlin code before Java. There could be a circular dependency issue, right? Normally, I believe compileKotlin happens before compileJava, and the classpath for compileJava includes the Kotlin output. That way, Java can reference Kotlin classes. Hmm, I should look up some Java tests to see if they utilize Kotlin classes from the same source. That's an interesting area to explore!
